  {
    "text": "hello i'm aman a cloud support engineer",
    "start": "12480",
    "end": "15280"
  },
  {
    "text": "here at the aws office in northern",
    "start": "15280",
    "end": "17520"
  },
  {
    "text": "virginia today i am going to show you a",
    "start": "17520",
    "end": "20320"
  },
  {
    "text": "few ways to deal with an issue when your",
    "start": "20320",
    "end": "22640"
  },
  {
    "text": "amazon elastic compute cloud instance is",
    "start": "22640",
    "end": "25359"
  },
  {
    "text": "stuck in the stopping state let's get",
    "start": "25359",
    "end": "27599"
  },
  {
    "text": "started",
    "start": "27599",
    "end": "29599"
  },
  {
    "text": "if your instance appears to be stuck in",
    "start": "29599",
    "end": "31599"
  },
  {
    "text": "the stopping state there might be an",
    "start": "31599",
    "end": "33680"
  },
  {
    "text": "issue with the underlying host hardware",
    "start": "33680",
    "end": "35920"
  },
  {
    "text": "in such a situation you can attempt to",
    "start": "35920",
    "end": "38079"
  },
  {
    "text": "recover the ec2 instance either by",
    "start": "38079",
    "end": "40160"
  },
  {
    "text": "performing a force stop or by launching",
    "start": "40160",
    "end": "42559"
  },
  {
    "text": "a replacement instance",
    "start": "42559",
    "end": "45440"
  },
  {
    "start": "45000",
    "end": "99000"
  },
  {
    "text": "you can force stop the ec2 instance",
    "start": "45440",
    "end": "47760"
  },
  {
    "text": "using either the aws management console",
    "start": "47760",
    "end": "50399"
  },
  {
    "text": "or the aws command line interface",
    "start": "50399",
    "end": "53920"
  },
  {
    "text": "follow these steps to force stop the ec2",
    "start": "53920",
    "end": "56399"
  },
  {
    "text": "instance using the aws management",
    "start": "56399",
    "end": "58559"
  },
  {
    "text": "console",
    "start": "58559",
    "end": "60480"
  },
  {
    "text": "log in to the aws management console and",
    "start": "60480",
    "end": "63440"
  },
  {
    "text": "navigate to the ec2 console",
    "start": "63440",
    "end": "66640"
  },
  {
    "text": "in the navigation pane choose instances",
    "start": "66640",
    "end": "70479"
  },
  {
    "text": "and select the stuck instance",
    "start": "70479",
    "end": "73680"
  },
  {
    "text": "choose instant state",
    "start": "73680",
    "end": "76320"
  },
  {
    "text": "for stop the instance",
    "start": "76320",
    "end": "79360"
  },
  {
    "text": "stop",
    "start": "79360",
    "end": "81439"
  },
  {
    "text": "to force stop the instance using the aws",
    "start": "81439",
    "end": "84159"
  },
  {
    "text": "cli use the stop instances command and",
    "start": "84159",
    "end": "87439"
  },
  {
    "text": "the dash dash force option like this",
    "start": "87439",
    "end": "91520"
  },
  {
    "text": "this forces the instance to stop within",
    "start": "91520",
    "end": "93920"
  },
  {
    "text": "a few minutes",
    "start": "93920",
    "end": "95680"
  },
  {
    "text": "you can then restart the ec2 instance",
    "start": "95680",
    "end": "99840"
  },
  {
    "start": "99000",
    "end": "284000"
  },
  {
    "text": "can create a replacement instance",
    "start": "99840",
    "end": "102640"
  },
